
# CHANGELOG


## [3.0.0] - 2025-07-21

### Changed

 - the library name officially changed to Jmenu.
 - the library returns class instead function now, so instead of let menu = handy(...) => let menu = new Jmenu();
 - `target` atttribute when creating a new menu, may accept a text selector for custom element groupe.
 - `stickto` attribute replace by two new attributes `alignToTarget` which may take boolean | "left" or | "right", and `alignToOffset` may take a number to offset alignment.
 - qway dependencies removed.
 - `.toggleButton` remove and replace by two separated `.enableButton` and `.disableButton`

### Added

 - new `.on` function to listen to event
 - new `.off` function to remove event listeners
 - new `.trigger` function to trigger events
 - interducing basic events trigger through out the system, `open` `close` with JmenuEvent objects
 - new `.setButtonProp` function to modify button's properties
 - new `.enableButton` to enable button
 - new `.disableButton` to disable button